# Testing standards

When the user asks for tests, write **well-structured, isolated** tests following the ItemsService patterns:

## File layout

- **One concern per file** ‚Äî e.g. `item.create.test.ts`, `getItem.test.ts`, `getReviews.test.ts`, not one giant catch-all suite.
- **Service unit tests** ‚Äî `item.service.test.ts`, `review.service.test.ts`: mock the DB layer with `vi.hoisted` + `vi.mock`, test delegation and error mapping only.
- **DB unit tests** ‚Äî `item.db.test.ts`, `review.insert.test.ts`: mock `pool.query`, cover branches (empty rows, `rowCount`, etc.).
- **Integration tests** ‚Äî dedicated files per GraphQL operation/flow; shared setup via `beforeAll` + `resetSchema()`, helpers in `test/helpers.ts`.

## Isolation

- Reset DB schema per suite (`db.resetSchema()`), not full `data.sql` unless required.
- Stub auth with `stubLoginFetch()`; use `createItemViaGraphql` and similar helpers instead of duplicating GraphQL strings.
- Mock external deps (login `fetch`, `pool`) in unit tests; do not hit real services in unit tests.
- Use `vi.unstubAllGlobals()` in `afterAll` when stubbing `fetch`.

## Quality

- Clear `describe` / `it` names that state behavior, not implementation.
- Assert outcomes (return shape, persistence, auth errors), not just ‚Äúno throw‚Äù.
- Cover happy path, auth failures, and important error branches.
- Keep tests independent within a file; avoid order-dependent state when possible.

## Copy-paste detection (CPD) ‚Äî always aim for zero

**Always try to get no CPD** (`jscpd` must pass with 0% duplication). After adding or changing tests, run the package‚Äôs CPD check (e.g. `npm run cpd` in `Service/ItemsService`, or root `npm run cpd-items`) and fix any clones before finishing.

- **Extract shared code** ‚Äî server bootstrap, `stubLoginFetch`, GraphQL helpers, and auth assertions live in `test/helpers.ts` (and `test/db.ts`), not copy-pasted across files.
- **Avoid duplicate blocks** ‚Äî repeated `beforeAll` / `afterAll`, identical supertest + query strings, or mirrored test bodies across files will fail CI; refactor into helpers or a small shared setup module instead.
- **Differentiate when you must repeat structure** ‚Äî vary naming, queries, or assertions so similar flows are not token-identical; prefer one helper with parameters over two nearly identical tests.
- **Do not ‚Äúfix‚Äù CPD by disabling the check** ‚Äî reduce duplication in the tests (or shared production code if that is the source).
